    // (forceLegacyHlsDemux = false), which plays the widest range of
    // providers -- including Xtream panels whose .m3u8 playlists the legacy
    // demuxer can't parse (confirmed: Tomek's nxtplay.xyz portal -- the mini
    // player, which never forced legacy, played fine while the full player,
    // which did, span forever). If an HLS stream soft-fails (EncounteredError),
    // we flip this to true ONCE and let the reconnect retry with ":demux=hls"
    // (legacy), which is more tolerant of some spec violations and was the
    // original workaround for the Tesla 2K TV SegmentList::updateWith SIGABRT.
    // Reset to false on every new channel so a working stream never gets the
    // legacy demuxer forced on it by an unrelated reconnect.
    @Volatile private var forceLegacyHlsDemux = false
    /**
     * True if the current stream is HLS (m3u8 playlist).
     *
     * Escape valve for HLS-specific routing. Today it gates one thing:
     * forcing libVLC's legacy `hls` demuxer over the newer adaptive one,
     * to dodge a known SegmentList::updateWith assertion crash on malformed
     * live playlists (one confirmed report on Tesla 2K TV, Android 11).
     *
     * Kept as a property -- not inlined -- so if we ever need a separate
     * code path for HLS (different reconnect logic, different cache
     * settings, different player engine even), there's one conditional to
     * hang it on. Free until we use it.
     */
    private val isHlsUrl: Boolean
